        "title": "feat: add meeting notes plugin",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds the generic Meeting Notes plugin with the meeting_notes tool, transcript artifact storage, heuristic summary rendering, and manual transcript import.\n- Adds the public plugin SDK meeting-notes source-provider contract and registry wiring so Discord, Google Meet, Slack huddles, and future sources can feed one notes engine.\n- Wires Discord voice as the first live meeting-notes source, using capture-only transcript handling when a notes session starts through the provider.\n- Documents the plugin, source model, SDK contract, Slack huddle path, and manifest/labeler surfaces.\n\n## Verification\n\n- pnpm test extensions/meeting-notes/index.test.ts extensions/discord/src/voice/meeting-notes-source.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/registry.contract.test.ts\n- node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -b tsconfig.projects.json\n- node scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs\n- env -u OPENCLAW_TESTBOX pnpm check:changed\n- git diff --check\n- node scripts/check-changelog-attributions.mjs\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: OpenClaw now has a generic meeting-notes plugin and SDK source-provider seam; Discord voice can start a live notes capture, and transcripts can be imported and summarized without channel-specific logic in the notes engine.\nReal environment tested: local macOS checkout with Node/pnpm repo tooling; focused Vitest shards; local changed gate across core, extension, docs, and tooling lanes.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: env -u OPENCLAW_TESTBOX pnpm check:changed\nEvidence after fix: check:changed completed successfully after conflict-marker, changelog attribution, dependency pin, shrinkwrap, sidecar loader, tsgo, oxlint, and import-cycle checks; focused meeting-notes and Discord source tests passed.\nObserved result after fix: manual transcript import writes transcript and summary artifacts; Discord source provider starts the voice manager in meeting-notes mode and forwards final utterances to the generic store callback.\nWhat was not tested: live Discord guild audio capture with real bot credentials; Google Meet and Slack huddle providers are documented future source adapters, not implemented live sources in this PR.\n",
